This paper investigates the Twitter interaction patterns of journals from the Science Citation Index (SCI) of Master Journal List (MJL), which involves the analysis of social media data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves network analysis, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Development and Programming), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper also discusses the differences between the Twitter usage of SCI journals with Humanities and Social Sciences (HSS) journals, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
